<1ST_LINE>r i BC-Gorbachev-KeyQuotes     06-28 0421</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Gorbachev-Key Quotes,0429</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Key Quotes From Mikhail S. Gorbachev's Party Conference
^With PM-Soviet-Party, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are key quotations from Soviet leader Mikhail
S. Gorbachev's opening address Tuesday to the 19th Communist Party
Conference.
   _ On farming:
   ``We must restore the economic balance between town and
countryside, and release to the utmost the potential of collective
and state farms by promoting diverse contractual and lease
arrangements.
   ``We must make the farmer sovereign master, protect him against
command methods and cardinally change the conditions of life in
villages. That is the only way to rapidly heighten the efficiency
of the agro-industrial sectors, and to secure a radical improvement
in food supplies across the country.''
   _ On economic reforms and price increases:
   ``The pricing reform cannot fail to affect retail prices as
well, because they are closely connected with the system of prices
as a whole. Today the retail price of many food products, notably
that of meat and milk, is considerably lower than the actual cost
of producing them, lower than the state's procurement price.
   ``The state is compelled to cover this difference in the form of
a subsidy to the consumer. That is not a normal situation. It
undermines the incentives for producing these products and gives
rise to a wasteful attitude, especially towards bread.
   ``We know all this perfectly well, comrades. It is absolutely
necessary, therefore, to resolve this problem no matter how
difficult it may be and no matter what doubts and fears it may
create at first glance.''
   _ On human rights:
   ``Now about the personal rights of citizens. Here, too, there is
a need for more precise legislative regulation.''
   ``Our entire legal system is designed to guarantee strict
observance of the rights of citizens to the inviolability of their
private life, home, the secrecy of telephone communication, postal
and telegraph correspondence. The law must reliably protect a
person's dignity.''
   _ On the establishment of the post of president of the Supreme
Soviet, or parliament:
    ``In the opinion of the CPSU Central Committe, establishing the
post of President of the U.S.S.R. Supreme Soviet would be in line
with enhancing the role played by the supreme bodies and by the
entire system of the Soviets of People's Deputies, strengthening
the rule-of-law basis of government and improving the
representation of the Soviet Union in world affairs.
   ``It should be ruled that the President shall be elected and
recalled by secret ballot by, and be fully answerable and
accountable to, the Congress of the U.S.S.R. People's Deputies.''
</TEXT>
