<HEAD>Group Says Member of Alternative Political Party Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A leading member of an alternative political party
has been arrested and sentenced to 15 days in jail for taking part
in a demonstration, a group spokesman said today.
   Yuri Mityunov, spokesman for the Democratic Union, said the
arrest was aimed at keeping the Democratic Union quiet during the
national Communist Party conference, which opened today.
   Mityunov said in a telephone call that Igor Tsarkov was arrested
at his workplace at a Moscow computer center Monday and sentenced
later that day by a court to 15 days in jail.
   Tsarkov was charged with taking part in an illegal demonstration
June 11, Mityunov said.
   At the Communist Party conference, Mikhail S. Gorbachev said in
an opening speech he would not tolerate alternative political
parties in the Soviet Union.
   Mityunov says the Democratic Union, which advocates a
multi-party sytem, has about 200 members nationwide, most of them
in Moscow and Leningrad. It was founded in May.
