<2ND_LINE>PM-Helms-Surgery,90</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Senator Recovering After Prostate Operation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. Jesse Helms, R-N.C., underwent prostate
surgery on Monday and is recovering, his Senate office said today.
   Helms, 66, one of the Senate's most conservative members,
entered Bethesda Naval Hospital in suburban Maryland on Sunday,
according to Barbara Lukens, his press secretary.
   She said there were no complications and that the senator is
expected to return to his Senate responsibilities later in the week.
   Helms is the ranking Republican member of the Senate Foreign
Relations Committee.
</TEXT>
