<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--StolenFireworks     06-28 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Stolen Fireworks,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Forest Lake's July 4 May Be Quiet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FOREST LAKE, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six cases of explosives intended for
Forest Lake's Fourth of July celebration were stolen from a
warehouse, authorities said.
   ``We hope to get them back, but we hope they didn't fall into
the wrong hands. Any hands are the wrong hands, but we just hope
they aren't kids,'' said Larry Kiefat of the Forest Lake American
Legion Post, who is in charge of the celebration.
   The explosives are worth about $3,500, he said.
   ``I usually store them somewhere else, locked up where nobody
knows where they are,'' Kiefat said.
   He said he ordered new fireworks from Appleton, S.D., hoping
they will arrive in time.
   Police Sgt. Mike Aschenbrener said it appears thieves broke in
through a back door.
   ``We've got one witness lead we're working on, but nothing
concrete yet,'' Aschenbrener said. ``We're hoping that anyone with
information will contact the Forest Lake police. Anybody setting
them off without proper training could be seriously injured.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
