<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Shooting     06-28 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Italy-Shooting,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gunmen Kill Three in Crowded Outdoor Market</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two gunmen opened fire in a crowded
outdoor market in this Sicilian city on Tuesday, killing three
people and sending panicked shoppers scrambling for cover,
authorities said.
   The three victims were waiting on customers at a clothes booth
when the gunmen pushed through the crowd and began shooting, police
said. His motive was not known.
   Giuseppe Lo Jacono, 15, and Giuseppe Cina, 28, died at the
scene. Another victim, Enrico Calandra, 23, died en route to the
hospital.
   No passers-by were injured in the shooting, but many ran
screaming into nearby shops or hid behind parked cars, authorities
said. The open-air market is held every Tuesday in a largely
residential area.
   The gunmen escaped on a motorscooter, which police later found
abandoned and burned on a nearby street.
</TEXT>
