<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--WoundedBuffalo     06-28 0177</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Wounded Buffalo,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fatally Wounded Buffalo Kills Hunter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hunter was gored to death by a fatally
wounded buffalo he was tracking through the bush, friends said
Tuesday.
   Clive Swemmer died en route to a hospital in the town of Kariba,
according to friends, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   He was hunting in the Zambezi Valley bordering Zambia on Friday
when a friend accompanying him shot and wounded the buffalo.
   Swemmer plunged into thick bush after the injured and angered
animal to put it out of its misery, the friends said. The buffalo
apparently turned on him and gored him before it died beside him.
   Swemmer, winner of the 1982 Zimbabwe Tobacco Grower of the Year
Award, farmed in the Macheke area about 60 miles from the Zimbabwe
capital of Harare.
   A state National Parks and Wildlife Management Department
spokesman official cautioned hunters against pursuing wounded
buffalo, saying: ``It's well know that they conceal themselves in
the bush and lie in wait to ambush the hunter, very often with
fatal results.''
</TEXT>
