<HEAD>McCausland Named to Head Defense Logistics Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan has nominated Air Force Lt.
Gen. Charles McCausland to become director of the Defense Logistics
Agency, the Pentagon said Tuesday.
   Assuming Senate confirmation, McCausland, 53, would replace Army
Lt. Gen. Vincent M. Russo, who will retire on Jan. 1, 1989.
   McCausland, a native of Flushing, N.Y., now is vice commander of
the Air Force Logistics Command.
   Russo, 57, from New York City, has headed the logistics agency
since July 1986 and will retire after more than 36 years of
active-duty service, the Pentagon said.
