<HEAD>Military Exercise Planned for August in California Desert</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 28,000 military personnel will
participate in an August military exercise in California sponsored
by the U.S. Central Command, the organization that oversees
American forces in the Mideast, the Pentagon said Tuesday.
   Exercise ``Gallant Eagle,'' which rotates each year between the
United States and Mideast countries such as Egypt, will be staged
Aug. 2-9 primarily at the Marine Corps installations of Camp
Pendleton, Calif., and Twentynine Palms, Calif.
   ``The exercise is intended to provide a simulated combat
environment to exercise, train and evaluate the U.S. Central
Command headquarters and units of its service components in
tactical employment operations in a desert environment,'' the
Pentagon said.
   ``Deployment operations for the exercise will begin from bases
throughout the country in early July.''
