<2ND_LINE>AM-Vicki Paisley-Payments CORRECTIVE,0107</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Papers that published a0763 of June 24, AM-Vicki
Paisley-Payments under a Washington dateline, are asked to publish
the following.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously reported June
24 that Vicki Paisley, wife of former Navy procurement chief Melvyn
Paisley, was paid up to $50,000 in 1986 by a firm linked to William
Galvin, a central figure in the Pentagon bribery investigation.
   Official records show that Mrs. Paisley was paid by the firm,
VAMO Inc. However, those records do not show how much she was paid.
Instead, the records show her ownership interest in the firm was
worth between $15,000 and $50,000.
