<1ST_LINE>r f PM-AMInternational     06-28 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-AM International,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>AM International To Sell Press Division</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   AM International Inc. says it has tentatively
agreed to sell its Harris Graphics Web Press Group to a Japanese
printing company in a deal valued at around $250 million.
   Marion G. Durk, vice president of the Chicago company, said
Monday that AM International signed a letter of intent to sell the
unit to Komori Printing Machinery Co. of Tokyo.
   But he said the company would continue to hold discussions with
a number of other businesses that have shown an interest in buying
the division.
   Under the agreement, Komori would pay $181 million in cash and
assume $52 million in debt. The deal also calls for Komori to
transfer back to the company its 3.9 million common shares of AM
International.
   AM International said the sale of its graphics unit would allow
it to lower its debt, invest in new businesses and raise its
shareholder dividends.
</TEXT>
